        "tab_qHR8en": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "90-Day Guarantee",
            "content": "<p>We offer a <strong>90-day money-back guarantee.</strong></p><p>If for any reason you're not completely satisfied with your sleep, we'll issue a <strong>full refund, no questions asked.</strong> Just reach out to our support team and we'll take care of it. Try Rejuvia risk-free — if it doesn't work for you, you don't pay.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_g7xhNe": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why Rejuvia Works",
            "content": "<p>Most sleep aids are pills or gummies, which means they have to survive your digestive system. Over 60–90 minutes your stomach breaks them down, destroying much of the active ingredients before they ever reach your bloodstream.</p><p>Rejuvia is a sublingual spray. You spray it under your tongue, where the ingredients absorb directly into your bloodstream — no digestion, no waiting, no waste. Your body absorbs up to <strong>75% more</strong> of the active sleep compounds compared to gummies and pills, which is why most customers are asleep within 10–15 minutes instead of 60–90.</p><p>We also use a low <strong>2mg dose of melatonin</strong> (most gummies pack 5–10mg, the cause of the morning hangover) paired with 12 natural sleep herbs that calm the mind without knocking you out cold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_LXTWYP": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Shipping & Returns",
            "content": "<p>Orders ship within 1 business days, with free shipping on all orders over $69. You'll receive tracking as soon as your order is on its way.</p><p>Not happy? Our 90-day money-back guarantee has you covered. Contact our support team for a full refund or any return assistance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_9V4YxW": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is Rejuvia Safe?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. Rejuvia is <strong>drug-free, non-habit-forming, and made with 100% natural ingredients.</strong> Because it works with your body's natural sleep cycle instead of overriding it, there's no tolerance buildup, no dependency, and no withdrawal.</p><p>Every batch is <strong>triple lab-tested for purity</strong> — no artificial dyes, added sugars, synthetic fillers, or mystery compounds. As always, if you're pregnant, nursing, taking medication, or have a medical condition, check with your healthcare provider first.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_MtCWCt": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Ingredients",
            "content": "<p>Rejuvia is a blend of <strong>13 natural sleep ingredients:</strong> melatonin (just 2mg), 5-HTP, valerian root, passionflower, chamomile, lemon balm, skullcap, magnolia bark, hops, cramp bark, ginkgo biloba, peppermint, and feverfew.</p><p>No fillers. No junk. No drugs. Just clean, naturally-sourced ingredients designed to quiet a racing mind and deliver deep, restorative sleep.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_QtT6wh": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
            "content": "<p><strong>What if it doesn't work for me?</strong> </p><p>You're covered by our 90-day money-back guarantee — full refund, no questions asked.</p><p><strong>Will I wake up groggy?</strong> </p><p>No. Our low 2mg melatonin dose is designed to give you restful sleep without the morning hangover from high-dose gummies and pills.</p><p><strong>How fast does it work?</strong> </p><p>Most customers fall asleep within 10–15 minutes of their nightly sprays.</p><p><strong>Is it habit-forming?</strong> </p><p>No. Rejuvia is drug-free and non-habit-forming, with no tolerance buildup or dependency.</p><p><strong>What flavor is it?</strong> </p><p>A light, pleasant natural mint taste that most customers genuinely enjoy.</p><p><strong>How long does one bottle last?</strong> </p><p>Roughly one month of nightly use, depending on your dosage.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
